<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Head of Confederation of Trade Unions Protests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Head of Confederation of Trade Unions Protests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3103213594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1930 GMT 31 Mar </F>

<F P=103> LD3103213594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1930 GMT 31 Mar </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alojz Englis, the president of the Confederation of 
Trade Unions, has sent a letter to Finance Minister Rudolf 
Filkus, drawing his attention to the violation of trade union 
freedoms as outlined in the accord of the International Labor 
Organization on the freedom of association and the protection of 
trade unions' right of association. In his letter, Alojz Englis 
stressed that the Finance Ministry fundamentally violated trade 
union rights by a decision calling on the trade unions that are 
members of the confederation to present their account books 
outlining their assets to appropriate tax bodies by 31 March. 
Englis pointed out that he will inform the international trade 
union headquarters about this, and, if the Finance Ministry does 
not change its stance, he will forward an official complaint to 
the International Labor Organization about the violation of 
trade union rights in Slovakia. 

</TEXT>

