<H3> <TI>   Grachev Expresses `Satisfaction' With Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev Expresses `Satisfaction' With Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3003152394 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1300 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3003152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Army General Pavel Grachev, Russian minister of 
defense, ended his official visit to Romania today with a joint 
news conference together with his Romanian counterpart Gheorghe 
Tinca. Both sides expressed satisfaction with the results of 
the visit. 
  The Russian guest and his retinue were received during their 
stay in Romania by President Ion Iliescu, Prime Minister Nicolae 
Vacaroiu, and Teodor Melescanu, minister of state and minister 
of foreign affairs. Likewise, the Russian defense minister and 
the Romanian minister of national defense, Gheorghe Tinca, 
signed an accord between the Ministry of National Defense of 
Romania and the Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation on 
the military cooperation between the two countries, which was 
considered by both sides as a start for relaunching the overall 
bilateral relations. 

