Daily Report 
<DATE1>  1 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gligorov Receives U.S. General Shalikashvili </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gligorov Receives U.S. General Shalikashvili </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104125194 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0104125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Shalikashvili-Gligorov Meeting"] </F>
  [Text] Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] President Kiro Gligorov received yesterday 
U.S. Chief of Joint Staff General John Shalikashvili. The 
meeting was also attended by Foreign Minister Crvenkovski and 
Defense Minister Popovski. They expressed satisfaction with the 
role of the U.S. contingent serving as members of UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] in Macedonia thus far, and discussed 
replacing the Nordic contingent with another American unit. 
They also exchanged ideas on the situation in the region and 
President Gligorov stressed the importance of resolving the 
Greek-Macedonian dispute, saying it could destabilize the south 
of the Balkans. Gligorov again actualized Macedonia's request to 
be included in the project "Partnership for Peace." 
  General Shalikashvili pointed out his country's interest in 
a 
stable Macedonia as an exceptionally significant factor of 
stability in the Balkans. He also announced appointment of U.S. 
Army representative to Macedonia in the near future. 
  General Shalikashvili also visited U.S. soldiers in 
Macedonia 
and patrol units on the Macedonian-Serbian border. 

</TEXT>

