<F P=103> AU3103195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 31 (CTK) -- Top bodies of the 
Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia [KSCM] have assumed a 
totally confrontational policy which practically deprives them 
of any possibility of constructive dialogue with other left-wing 
parties, Left Bloc Party (SLB) Chairwoman Marie Stiborova told 
journalists today. 
  She was reacting to remarks made by KSCM Chairman Miroslav 
Grebenicek during the KSCM Central Committee meeting on last 
Saturday [26 March] in which he said, among other things, that 
SLB and the People's National and Social Salvation Union 
(LUNSZ), led by the pre-November 1989 Czechoslovak Communist 
Party Prague branch chairman Miroslav Stepan, tried to feed on 
KSCM structures. 
  The Czechoslovak Communist Party was disbanded in April 
1992. 
  In view of last weekend's meeting of the Democratic Left 
Party (SDL) National Council, which decided against sharing an 
election staff with the SLB, the two parties will form a common 
election coordination council. 
  The SLB Central Committee, scheduled to meet on April 8, is 
to discuss the creation of an election staff. 
  "We see the elections as being based on the civic principle. 
We are also aware that in many places, people have asked that 
the left insist on its candidates having adequate 
qualifications," Stiborova said. 

</TEXT>

