<H3> <TI>   Polls Show Support for Center, Right </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Polls Show Support for Center, Right </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103114394 Prague CTK in English 0849 GMT 31 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3103114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 31 (CTK) -- Most Czechs support the 
middle ground in politics or are right of center; only two 
percent support the extreme left wing and five percent the 
extreme right, according to the results of a recent poll 
conducted by the Institute for Public Opinion Research (IVVM). 
  Respondents were asked to define their position on the 
political spectrum with numbers from 1, signifying extreme left 
wing, to seven, the extreme right. Twenty-nine percent described 
themselves as centrist, 38 percent right of center and 17 
percent left of center. Nine percent had no opinion. 
  A higher number of those identifying themselves as right of 
center are in the 30-44 age group or are entrepreneurs, while 
the position finds less support among people over 60 and 
workers. IVVM polled 1,559 people over the age of fifteen. 

</TEXT>

