BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 31 March (MTI) -- Prime Minister of the 
Russian Federation Viktor Chernomyrdin, arriving Thursday [31 
March] morning for a two-day official visit, was received with 
military honors in front of the Parliament building. 
  Following the ceremony, the Russian prime minister held an 
hour-long private meeting with his host, Prime Minister Peter 
Boross. After the meeting, Hungarian and Russian negotiating 
delegations opened talks under the chairmanship of the two prime 
ministers. 
  Hungarian Minister of International Economic Relations Bela 
Kadar and his Russian counterpart, Oleg Davidov, chaired a 
session of the Hungarian-Russian inter-governmental committee on 
trade and economic cooperation. 
  Kadar said the main topic discussed was the debt Russia owes 
Hungary and possible forms of repayment, adding that an 
agreement has been reached in principle on the means of 
repayment and possible Hungarian participation in Russian 
privatization. 

</TEXT>

