<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 31 -- Polish parliamentary delegation 
visit to Romania that ended on Wednesday "should break the 
political and economic deadlock in Polish-Romanian contacts," 
Senate Speaker Adam Struzik said on Thursday. 
  He added that during the talks of the delegation with 
Romanian leading politicians, the Romanian side made it clear 
that the contacts between the two countries have weakened 
recently. Struzik hopes that after his forthcoming talks with 
the Polish prime minister and the minister for foreign economic 
relations the relations will be intensified. 
  According to Struzik, Romania can be Poland's good economic 
partner. 

