<H3> <TI>   Hungarian Office Chief Visits, Discusses Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hungarian Office Chief Visits, Discusses Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103175594 Budapest MTI in English 1616 GMT 31 Mar 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3103175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 31 Mar (MTI) -- State Secretary Geza 
Entz, president of the Office of Hungarians Beyond the Border, 
at a Thursday meeting in Cluj conferred the Middle Cross of the 
Republic of Hungary Merit of Order on Samu Benko, cultural 
historian and chairman of the Transylvanian Museum Association, 
on behalf of President Arpad Goncz. Benko has gained 
distinction as a researcher and publicist in preserving the 
cultural identity of Hungarians in Romania. 
  During his tour in Transylvania, Entz met representatives of 
the Hungarian Democratic Union of Romania and other Hungarian 
organizations with whom he discussed how Hungarian aid had been 
used and what future changes and improvement should be 
introduced. The state secretary also met senior officials from 
over 30 foundations. 

</TEXT>

