<H3> <TI>   Moravcik on `Immoral' Privatization Deal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik on `Immoral' Privatization Deal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103083994 Prague CTK in English 0702 GMT 31 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3103083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 31 (CTK) -- A privatization deal 
approved by Vladimir Meciar's government shortly before it was 
unseated by a vote of no-confidence deprived the state of about 
a billion Slovak crowns ($31 million), Premier Jozef Moravcik 
said on Slovak television on Wednesday, the Czech daily RUDE 
PRAVO reports today. 
  Speaking in the weekly debate programme "Slobodny piatok," 
Moravcik, who succeeded Meciar as premier on March 16, said the 
outgoing government sold a ten percent stake in the East Slovak 
Steelworks, VSZ Kosice, to a private company at 20 percent of 
the nominal value. 
  In the programme Moravcik was answering the questions of 
Slovak and foreign journalists for the first time since his 
appointment. He called the sale by Meciar's government immoral 
in view of the financial losses caused to Slovakia, RUDE PRAVO 
reports. 

</TEXT>

