<H3> <TI>   Serb Attack on Gorazde, Mostar Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Attack on Gorazde, Mostar Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Silajdzic Condemns Lack of Reaction </H4>

<F P=102> AU0104200394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0104200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Mladen Bosnjak report on the statements by </F>
Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic and Raymond 
Flynn, U.S. ambassador to the Vatican, in Sarajevo on 1 April -- 
recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [Bosnjak] Mr. Silajdzic stressed at the 
beginning of his statement that the arrival of Raymond Flynn, 
U.S. ambassador to the Vatican, again confirmed the interest of 
Bill Clinton and Holy Father Pope John Paul II in the situation 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina. Then he said: 
  [Silajdzic] As for me, unfortunately I had to tell the 
ambassador about some things that do not sound very optimistic, 
generally speaking, and asked him to convey this to the highest 
authorities. What I said is that the continuation of the peace 
process is endangered with the latest attacks on Gorazde -- a 
massive offensive is under way, and many people are being 
killed, innocent people; with the attacks on Bihac, and the 
ethnic cleansing, the new wave of ethnic cleansing -- against 
which President Izetbegovic protested yesterday -- that is 
taking place in Bosnian Krajina. 
  Today I received information from the chairman of the 
International Red Cross, responsible for central Bosnia and 
Bosnian Krajina, who said that we have to either protect the 
6,000 people in Prijedor and the surrounding area or move them 
out. Their lives are in danger. This is very bad news. 
  In connection with Gorazde, the international community is 
silent about it. A zone that has been proclaimed protected by a 
UN Security Council resolution is under attack. An offensive is 
underway, and many people have been killed. I am certain that 
the UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] in Bosnia-Herzegovina can 
follow the development of the situation, they can see it on 
their television here in Sarajevo, and their command knows very 
well what is going on. The United Nations has been informed; 
the Security Council has been informed. However, there is no 
reaction. The situation is repeating itself, where the 
aggressor is allowed to do almost anything he wants. I will 
repeat, the continuation of the peace negotiations has been 
seriously endangered with these latest activities by the 
aggressor in the region of Gorazde and Bihac, and the ethnic 
cleansing of the remaining non-Serbian population in Bosnian 
Krajina. 
  [Bosnjak] Ambassador Flynn expressed the concern and the 
understanding of the American people for the suffering of the 
people in Bosnia-Herzegovina, and spoke of the appeals and 
prayers of the Holy Father for the return of peace. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

