<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Confirms 19 Murders in Prijedor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104192394 Paris AFP in English 1905 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0104192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 1 (AFP) -- Seventeen Moslems and two 
Croats have been murdered in the Serb-controlled western Bosnian 
town of Prijedor in the past two days, Kris Janowski, spokesman 
for the UN High Commissioner for Refugees, said Friday [1 April]. 
  Janowski said he had received the figures from the Moslem 
humanitarian organisation Merhamet, but that a UNHCR official 
who had visited the town Friday said the figures were "probably 
right." 

</TEXT>

