<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Redman, Karadzic on `Territorial Arrangements' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Redman, Karadzic on `Territorial Arrangements' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103151494 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3103151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by SRNA journalist Mirjana Kusnik] </F>
  [Text] Charles Redman, the U.S. President's special envoy 
for the former Yugoslavia, and Radovan Karadzic, president of 
the Srpska republic, met in Pale today. In a statement for SRNA 
after the meeting, Redman pointed out that he had come to reach 
political and territorial arrangements, albeit without concrete 
offers. We are making efforts to solve territorial borders in 
Bosnia in a new way, because after the creation of the 
Muslim-Croatian federation, we want to hear what the Serb side 
intends to do, Redman said and added that borders are a great 
problem that will not be easy to solve. These are extremely 
great problems as the war has been waged for two years already 
and I do not think that the situation will improve soon, Redman 
said. 
  Karadzic reiterated the readiness of the Serbian side to 
(?support) every proposal for solving the crisis in the former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina which would not be contrary to the interests 
of the Serbian people. 
  Redman and Karadzic hailed the efforts Russia, the European 
Union, and the United Nations made with a way to solving the 
crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Speaking about the ceasing of clashes between the Croats and 
the Muslims, Redman said that a united Croat-Muslim army will 
probably be formed, as, in his opinion, this is the best 
solution to establishing peace between Croats and Muslims on 
their territories. 
  This afternoon in the Muslim part of Sarajevo, Redman will 
meet Alija Izetbegovic and convey to him the stands of the 
leadership of the Srpska republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

