<H3> <TI>   Abdic's Forces Attack Cazin Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abdic's Forces Attack Cazin Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0204211194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0204211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Bihac region tried to heal its wounds today 
after almost two months of the Serb aggressor's offensive. 
However, members of Abdic's paramilitary units stepped in to 
make up for somewhat lower intensity of attacks launched by 
Karadzic's terrorists. The chetniks began by launching an 
artillery attack on the defense lines on the Grmusa-Srbljani 
plateau on the Bihac part of the front. 
  Civilians were the victims of this madness again today. A 
16-year-old girl was killed by a sniper shot. Abdic's 
paramilitary forces, reinforced by their chetnik allies, resumed 
their destructive attacks. On this occasion they shelled 
industrial facilities in the Cazin municipality belonging to the 
meat industry Puran in Pjanici. These facilities were one of 
the most important parts of Agrokomerc [food processing company 
founded by Abdic] in the Cazin municipality before the war broke 
out. The autonomists also attempted infantry breakthroughs in 
the Pecigrad area. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

