<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cajnice-Foca-Gorazde Triangle Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cajnice-Foca-Gorazde Triangle Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0104111694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1027 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0104111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 1 Apr (TANJUG) -- Following a short 
overnight lull, fighting in the triangle between Cajnice, Foca 
and Gorazde continued unabated around 0500 today, even though an 
attempted Muslim breakthrough launched from Gorazde on Tuesday 
and Wednesday ended in complete failure, the command of the Serb 
forces announced. The command said that the fiercest fighting 
was in the region of Gradina hill. These are the fiercest 
Serb-Muslim clashes in this area since the beginning of the war, 
with both sides using all types of weapons. The surrounding 
mountains have been ringing with deafening explosions and 
incessant shooting. 
  Two Serb fighters were killed in almost hand-to-hand 
fighting 
yesterday. According to Serb Command estimates, about 100 
members of the Muslim units have been put out of action. 

</TEXT>

