<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatia Backing Muslim Offensive Against Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatia Backing Muslim Offensive Against Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0304150794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1419 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0304150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, April 3 (TANJUG) -- The all-out Moslem 
offensive on the Bosnian Serb republic continues on all fronts 
on Sunday, the Bosnian Serb command says and adds that along the 
Sava river in the north the Moslems are being backed by regular 
troops of neighbouring Croatia. 
  According to the same source, Croatian multiple rocket 
launchers and long-range artillery on the left bank of the Sava 
river have been pounding the territory of the Bosnian Serb 
republic. 
  The shelling has been especially heavy in the Serb villages 
of Krepsic and Obudovac and the town of Doboj. 
  The Bosnian Serb command says that although the Moslems are 
attacking practically all borders of the Bosnian Serb republic, 
the brunt of their attacks is directed against the corridor 
linking the eastern and the western part of the republic. 
  The same source emphasizes that the Bosnian Serb army is 
responding to all attacks and inflicting heavy losses to the 
enemy, and that everything indicates to a complete breakdown of 
the Moslem offensive very soon. 
  Moslem-controlled Radio Sarajevo reports continuation of 
inter-Moslem fighting in the northwest between forces loyal to 
Fikret Abdic and Moslem hardline leader Alija Izetbegovic. 
  Abdic, a fierce opponent of Izetbegovic's war-mongering 
policy, last October proclaimed independence for the province of 
western Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

