<H3> <TI>   TANJUG Report on Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TANJUG Report on Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404110394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0946 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0404110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Knin, 4 Apr (TANJUG) -- A cease-fire agreement 
between the Croatian Army and the Serb Krajina army covering a 
1,600-kilometer-long front came into effect at 0900 today. 
[passage omitted] 
  ISKRA reports, quoting a statement by Lieutenant Colonel 
Marinko Gajic, the assistant commander of the Serb Krajina army, 
that Serb Krajina army units have started withdrawing their 
heavy weapons and forces, and that on the Krajina side "there 
will be no problems in fully complying with the provisions of 
the Zagreb agreement." The same source said that UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] representatives reported that the Croatian 
side is also withdrawing its manpower and equipment. 

</TEXT>

