<H3> <TI>   Mostar Bosnians Stripped of Refugee Status </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mostar Bosnians Stripped of Refugee Status </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0204223594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2200 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0204223594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Office for Refugees of the Republic of Croatia 
has decided to strip all the citizens of Bosnia-Herzegovina who 
fled to Croatia from the Mostar area of their refugee status, 
B-H Press [Bosnia-Herzegovina state agency] reports. 
  Taking into account the fact that the roads are still closed 
and that parts of the Mostar region are still under occupation, 
a number of refugees from Mostar will have to go to a third 
country now instead of returning to their homes. 

</TEXT>

