  [Text] Defense Minister Antonin Baudys today received 
Dainis Turlajs, commander of the Latvian Armed Forces, at the 
end of his visit to the Czech Republic. The Latvian 
representative held talks on mutual cooperation in the armaments 
industry. He was interested mainly in the surplus and unusable 
equipment of the Czech Army. The Czech side will consider 
further his proposal to possibly provide this equipment to the 
Latvian Army, together with training support and teaching how to 
operate the equipment. 

