<H3> <TI>   Estimate Shows 0.3-Percent GDP Drop in 1993 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Estimate Shows 0.3-Percent GDP Drop in 1993 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104135094 Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Czech 31 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0104135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "joe": "Gross Domestic Product Declined 0.3 </F>
Percent in Real Terms Last Year"] 
  [Text] Prague--The Czech Republic's gross domestic product 
[GDP] declined by 0.3 percent in 1993, compared with 1992, in 
real terms. The Czech Statistical Office [CSU] estimates the 
total volume of GDP in current prices at 923.1 billion Czech 
korunas. As CSU Press Spokeswoman J. Lehnerova told our paper 
yesterday, the proportion of the nonstate sector in GDP reached 
more than 45 percent last year. The above data is only 
preliminary, Lehnerova said, because the information available 
at the time the estimate was made was not complete. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

