BFN 

  [Text] The cease-fire agreement signed in the Russian 
Embassy in Zagreb [on 30 March] between a Croatian delegation 
and the Serb rebels from the occupied Croatian areas came into 
effect at 0900 today. According to reports from the political 
department of the Split operational area, the cease-fire is 
being observed. 
  The Zadar-Biograd area is quiet today, as it was last night. 
The Sinj and Sibenik-Drnis areas are also quiet. 

</TEXT>

