  [Text] Gjirokaster, April 2 (ATA) -- Some 800 Albanians 
have been expelled from Greece over the Kakavije border crossing 
point during the past three days. The average number of 
expelles reached 230 a day. Some of the Albanians have been 
working in Greece for years with regular visas. They were 
abused, their money was confiscated, and their passports were 
torn to pieces. 

