  [Excerpts] Sofia, April 2 (BTA) -- "Elections promise to be 
a way out of the problems of the present moment, but there are 
almost no guarantees that voters will realize that fact," 
Bulgarian Socialist Party [BSP] leader Zhan Videnov told 
reporters in Plovdiv (the second largest town in Bulgaria, about 
120 km south-east of Sofia). According to him, there is little 
chance of forming a cabinet on a BSP mandate in this parliament. 
