<H3> <TI>   Belgium's Claes Arrives To Discuss EU, Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belgium's Claes Arrives To Discuss EU, Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0304164194 Sofia BTA in English 1543 GMT 3 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0304164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, April 3 (BTA) -- Belgium's Deputy Prime 
Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs Willy Claes arrived on 
an official visit here this afternoon. I would like to 
strengthen our bilateral relations but I must take the 
opportunity to discuss Bulgaria's contacts with the European 
Union as well as the problem of stability and security in 
Central Europe, he said upon his arrival. 
  Diplomatic relations between Bulgaria and Belgium were 
established in 1879 and were suspended between 1941 and 1947. 
The latest visit of a Belgian foreign minister to Bulgaria took 
place 10 years ago. In a televised interview last night 
Bulgaria's ambassador to Belgium, Ms. Lea Cohen, described the 
visit of Mr. Claes as a "revival of active contacts between 
Bulgaria and Belgium". 
  Tomorrow morning Mr. Claes will have talks at the Bulgarian 
Foreign Ministry. In the afternoon he will be received by 
President Zhelyu Zhelev, National Assembly Chairman Aleksandur 
Yordanov and acting Prime Minister Evgeni Matinchev. On Tuesday 
Mr. Claes, who has graduated from a music-school and has 
conducted almost all symphony orchesrtas in Belgium, will 
conduct the Sofia Philharmonic Orchestra in the National Palace 
of Culture. 

</TEXT>

