<F P=103> AU0104172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 1 (CTK) -- Head of the Latvian Armed 
Forces Dainis Turlais was today received at the end of his visit 
by Czech Defense Minister Antonin Baudys, the Defense Ministry 
Press Department told CTK. 
  During his three-day visit, Turlais has been negotiating 
cooperation between the Czech Republic and Latvia in the weapons 
industry. He showed most interest in the Czech army's excess 
equipment, and his suggestion that this equipment be offered to 
the Latvian Army, along with help in training will be given 
further consideration by the Czech Republic. 
  Turlais was also interested in the Czech soldier's 
experiences from taking part in peacekeeping missions. Latvia 
is interested in taking part in such international military 
activities as part of a joint Baltic force. He passed on to 
Baudys an invitation from the Latvian defense minister to visit 
Latvia. 

</TEXT>

