<H3> <TI>   MSZDP Holds News Conference on Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MSZDP Holds News Conference on Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0204180694 Budapest MTI in English 1711 GMT 2 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0204180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, April 2 (MTI) -- The Social Democratic 
Party of Hungary (MSZDP) will win seats in Hungarian Parliament 
in the course of the elections in May, party chairman Zoltan 
Kiraly said at the MSZDP's press conference on Saturday [2 
April]. 
  The party's National Board discussed the results achieved so 
far in the election campaign. It approved the national list, 
which so far has 15 candidates. The list is headed by party 
chairman Zoltan Kiraly, followed by academician Laszlo Kapolyi, 
third is MSZDP Secretary General Istvan Podkoniczky. 
  It was reported that the MSZDP was able to put up 
territorial 
lists in 11 counties by Saturday, and 46 of the 170 candidates 
have already collected more than the necessary 750 
recommendation slips. 
  In answer to a question, Kiraly said that even if the party 
does not attain the 5 per cent limit needed to enter parliament, 
he is confident that an MSZDP group can be created with 10 
individual MPs. 
  Kiraly said a social-liberal coalition of the Hungarian 
Socialist Party (MSZP) and the Alliance of Free Democrats 
(SZDSZ) has chances for victory at the elections. 

</TEXT>

