<H3> <TI>   Walesa Seeks Bank's Opinion on Budget Bill </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa Seeks Bank's Opinion on Budget Bill </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3103192594 Warsaw PAP in English 1415 GMT 31 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3103192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 31 -- President Lech Walesa has 
received President of the National Bank of Poland (NBP) Hanna 
Gronkiewicz-Waltz and NBP Vice-President Witold Kozinski to seek 
their opinion on the budget bill, the president's press office 
said. 
  Gronkiewicz-Waltz pointed out that the approval of the 
budget 
would open up an opportunity to negotiate another agreement with 
the International Monetary Fund (IMF). She said that the 
implementation of the previous agreement brought about the 
cancellation of 8 billion dollars owed to the Paris Club and 
contributed to a preliminary agreement on cancelling part of 
Poland's debt to the London Club. 
  She stressed that the signing of the agreement increased 
Poland's credibility in the international arena, reduced the 
level of Polish risk, created chances for the greater inflow of 
investment funds to Poland and made it possible to get another 
loan from the European Union (EU). 
  The president voiced its concern over lack of implementation 
of promises made during the election campaign by the present 
political alignment. Walesa said this was the problem making 
the president to be very cautious when making difficult decision 
concerning the budget. 

</TEXT>

