<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDSR Chairman Opposes Early Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PDSR Chairman Opposes Early Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104154294 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1241 GMT 1 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0104154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 1/4/1994 -- Local elections 
should precede legislative ones, irrespective if the latter are 
normal or early, Oliviu Gherman, chairman of the ruling party, 
the Social Democracy Party of Romania [PDSR], told a ROMPRES 
correspondent after the Thursday, March 31, meeting of the PDSR 
Standing Delegation. 
  Gherman said that the PDSR had a very clear point of view on 
snap elections. "Although we are not afraid of early elections, 
we deem they are counterproductive, it may even be dangerous to 
favor them," mentioned the politician. 
  The PDSR chairman expanded by saying that huge sums of money 
would be necessary for the organization of early elections this 
year, which is decisive for the reform and characterized by 
financial shrinking. Gherman opined that the political spectrum 
had not changed considerably since 1992 and mentioned that a new 
electoral law should be drafted. The 1992 polls were held in 
keeping with a law written uniquely for them, added Gherman. 
  According to the PDSR chairman, favoring early elections is 
tantamount to political frivolity. 

</TEXT>

