<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA Head Visits Magurele Nuclear Institute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Head Visits Magurele Nuclear Institute </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104145594 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 0918 GMT 1 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0104145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 1/4/1994 -- Hans Blix, IAEA 
[International Atomic Energy Agency] general director, currently 
on a visit to Romania, was the guest on 31 March of the Magurele 
Nuclear Engineering and Physics Institute near Bucharest. 
  On the occasion, the general director of the Nuclear Physics 
Institute (IFA), Professor Alexandru Glodeanu, presented the 
site, as well as the premises where the nuclear reactor is 
situated. Also visited were several labs where the guest could 
see a specialized computer program for the prediction of effects 
of a potential nuclear catastrophe and the dosimetric radiations 
lab, one of the key points in the institute. 
  The guest were also informed on the achievements of the 
center for the production of radio isotopes which are essential 
for collateral fields of physics. The Swedish guest was also 
presented the nuclear reactor built back in 1957, which almost 
doubled its capacity by successive modernization works, and the 
tandem linear accelerator regarded by the guest as a unique 
equipment in East Europe, which is producing heavy ions used in 
nuclear and atomic physics researches. 

</TEXT>

