<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rugova: `No Parallel' Between Kosovo, Krajina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rugova: `No Parallel' Between Kosovo, Krajina </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104183994 Tirana Radio Tirana Network in Albanian 1430 
GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0104183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana Radio Tirana Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Ibrahim Rugova, president of the republic of 
Kosova, held a news conference in Prishtina today. Here is a 
telephone report by our correspondent, Leke Musolli: 
  [Musolli] At the beginning of today's news conference, the 
president of the republic of Kosova, Dr. Ibrahim Rugova, 
welcomed the visit of Albanian President Dr. Sali Berisha to 
Great Britain and considered it as very important, as it focused 
on the situation in the region and particularly on the grave 
situation in Kosova. Our political project on Kosova, which is 
supported by all the Albanian political parties, is clear and 
derives from the 1991 plebiscite on Kosova as independent and 
neutral state. 
  Rugova said that despite attempts to prevent the 
internationalization of the Kosova question, even this week 
Kosova was at the center of attention of the international 
community and forums. On this occasion, he greeted the report 
of Amnesty International, which objectively describes the 
torture and recent imprisonments in Kosova and will help the 
world to understand the repressive and police situation in 
Kosova. 
  Rugova also greeted the report of the Helsinki Committee of 
the U.S. Congress on human rights and the bill presented by U.S. 
Congressmen Angle and Molinari, which seeks a solution for 
Kosova, precisely to stop the repression in Kosova. 
  Rugova also welcomed all the rallies of Albanians all over 
Europe, which helped to sensitize people to the Albanian 
question. 
  At today's news conference, Rugova informed reporters about 
the police repression that the Serbian authorities has recently 
been causing in Kosova. 
  Asked whether there are any indications of an Albanian-Serb 
dialogue, Rugova stressed that for the moment there are no such 
initiatives, but added that the Albanian side is ready for 
unconditional dialogue, internationally supervised. 
  Another reporter asked Rugova how he would comment on the 
threats by a parliamentary group from the Russian Duma, members 
of Zhirinovskiy's Liberal Democratic Party, who visited Kosova a 
few days ago. Rugova said that he considered such threats as a 
manifestation of Russian extremism but expressed his conviction 
that it did not present any serious problem. On the contrary, 
such forces are distressing for Yeltsin's power itself. 
  At today's news conference, the president of Kosova welcomed 
the agreement on the cease-fire between the representatives of 
Knin and the Croatian authorities. However, no parallel can be 
made between the problem of Knin and the Kosova question, the 
president of the republic of Kosova, Dr. Ibrahim Rugova, said at 
the end of today's news conference. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

