<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SNS: Molnar Not Sent by Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SNS: Molnar Not Sent by Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404173494 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0404173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak National Party [SNS] did not send its 
deputy chairman, Juraj Molnar, to the fifth Congress of the 
Liberal Democratic Party in Moscow. This was stated by SNS 
Chairman Jan Slota in an interview with TASR today. He said 
that Molnar had left as an observer for the world congress of 
Slav Orthodox and Christian nations with the consent of the SNS 
executive but without authorization to deliver any kind of 
message. 
  According to Jan Slota, the invitation to the congress of 
Slavs did not mention the Fifth Congress of the Russian Liberal 
Democrats. 
  The SNS chairman stressed that the SNS has not made any 
contacts with Zhirinovskiy's party nor has it the intention to 
do so in the future. 

</TEXT>

