<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Forces Break Through Gorazde Defense Lines </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Forces Break Through Gorazde Defense Lines </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404205294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0404205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Fahrudin Behic] </F>
  [Text] Unfortunately I have to send you bad news from 
Gorazde. After 10,000 shells of all calibers, after superhuman 
fighting and unprecedented heroism of the defenders, the defense 
line has been breached in the southern part of the battlefield 
on the right bank of the Drina. The situation is exceptionally 
dramatic, while fresh columns of refugees are moving into the 
town center from villages on the right bank. 
  The villages of Ahmovici, Uhotici, Kodzaga Polje, and some 
other villages from this area have been emptied of their 
inhabitants. Many civilians have been killed. Those who have 
succeeded in getting out in the face of strong aggressor forces, 
are trying to cross to the left bank and have somehow get into 
the town. In the town, however, the situation is extremely 
dramatic. 
  At about 1900, artillery shelling intensified. Howitzer 
shells are being used to systematically target houses one by one 
in Vitkovici, (Vaci), and (Vinarici). Many people have been 
killed. It is not possible to get information from the military 
hospital because everyone is involved there in giving help to 
the injured. 
  Infantry attacks also intensified at 2000 on the southern 
approaches to the town. No one knows what things will look like 
and what will happen in the night ahead. If anyone wants to 
help Gorazde they should do so immediately. For many people 
here tomorrow will be too late. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7695 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu065_i_94002" </HT>


