<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRY Soldiers Abduct, Release Border Patrol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRY Soldiers Abduct, Release Border Patrol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0404150494 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0404150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Police Patrol Seized"] </F>
  [Text] On 30 March 1994, around 1100, in the vicinity of 
the spot called Mecka near Kumanovo, three members of the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia's army abducted a three-member 
police patrol at the police station in Zeglane, reports the 
Ministry of Internal Affairs. The police patrol was on its 
regular duty when in the vicinity of Mecka they were surrounded 
by three members of the FRY army. The latter pointed their guns 
at the policemen and told them to leave the vehicle and to 
surrender. Their weapons were then taken and the patrol, 
together with their vehicle, were brought to the Prohor Pcinski 
border army station on Yugoslav territory. Somewhere around 2230 
on the same day, the patrol were set free and, together with the 
complete equipment, their arms and the vehicle, were delivered 
to the Macedonian border authorities. The incident took place 
on the territory of the Republic of Macedonia [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 350-400 meters off the 
border line. The Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Macedonia 
delivered a protest note to the Foreign Ministry of the Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia, expressing deep concern considering the 
fact that such incidents do not contribute to the establishment 
of regular friendly relations between the two neighboring 
countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

