<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgrade, April 5 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb forces 
confirmed Tuesday [5 April] they had broken through government 
defence lines in the eastern enclave of Gorazde in response to a 
government "offensive" and landed on the western bank of the 
Drina River. 
  In Geneva, the UN High Commissioner for Refugees said 50 
people had been killed and 250 injured since last week in the 
fighting in Goradze. 
  Chief of staff Manojlo Milovanovic told the Bosnian Serb 
agency SRNA he had ordered his troops to launch a 
"counter-attack" towards Cajnica, southeast of Gorazde, close to 
the Serbian border, late Monday since "Moslem formations were 
trying to join up with forces from Sarajevo and the other 
enclaves." 
  SRNA said that Moslem units had fallen back to the villages 
of Vitkovici and Mrvavici. [passage omitted] 
  Milovanovic said the Gorazde defenders were attempting "to 
join up with Sandzak and beyond that with Kosovo." [passage 
omitted] 

