<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Islamic Fanatics' Attack Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Islamic Fanatics' Attack Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0404142994 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0404142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Jelena Dabarcic report] </F>
  [Text] After a brief lull on the Gorazde front yesterday, 
the Muslim forces early this morning renewed their attacks on 
the positions of the Serbian fighters in the direction of Foca 
and Cajnice. Fierce artillery-infantry attacks are being waged 
in the regions of Podkozare, Paljike, and Oglecevo, where 
Islamic fanatics are trying to breach the defense lines of the 
Serbian territory at any cost. 
  The Serbian military sources claim that the Muslims have 
regrouped their forces at the part of the front between Gorazde, 
Cajnice, and Foca, and that they have abandoned the idea of 
making an advance toward Cajnice via Gradina and Trebecevo, 
where they suffered major losses in the past few days. 
  According to Colonel Jezdimir Lakicevic, on the seventh day 
of their offensive, the Muslim forces from Gorazde are not 
giving up their plan of linking up with their forces in Sarajevo 
and reaching the border with the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, 
and in this way realize their dream of establishing a green line 
linking Sarajevo, Gorazde, and Sandzak. 
  In the fighting that took place this morning, the Serbian 
side did not have any fatalities. Several fighters were wounded. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

