<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Offensive `Crushed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Offensive `Crushed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504115594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1102 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 5 Apr (TANJUG) -- The eight-day Muslim 
offensive launched from the direction of Gorazde towards the 
Serb territory in Srbinje (formerly Foca) and Cajnice has been 
crushed, while the units of the Srpska army have reached the 
right bank of the Drina River, Major General Manojlo 
Milovanovic, chief of the general staff of the Srpska army said 
today. 
  "Yesterday I ordered a counterattack to be carried out from 
the direction of Cajnice, because the Muslim units had 
persistently been trying to link up with their units in 
Sarajevo," Gen. Milovanovic said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

