<H3> <TI>   Silajdzic Supports Evacuation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Silajdzic Supports Evacuation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0304155794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0304155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bosnian Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic supports the 
plans of the International Committee of the Red Cross to 
evacuate non-Serb residents of Prijedor in order to protect them 
from violence. Human lives are most important, even if that 
helps the Serbs in their ethnic cleansing, Silajdzic told 
journalists. Around 9,000 Muslims and Croats and 55,000 Serbs 
live in Prijedor at the moment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7719 </DOCNO>
