<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Shelling Hits Usora Civilians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Shelling Hits Usora Civilians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404175294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0404175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] News from Bosnia-Herzegovina: The Serbs committed a 
new crime in Usora today. Shrapnel from a grenade fired by the 
Serbs wounded 13 civilians who were lining up for humanitarian 
aid, the department for political activites of the 110th brigade 
of the Usora Croatian Defense Council has announced. 
  Doctors in a hospital in Tesanj are fighting to save their 
lives. One child has already died from the shrapnel wounds. 
According to the same source, since 1300 this morning Serb 
artillery has been pounding the villages of the free Croatian 
community of Usora from several directions. A humanitarian aid 
convoy and the spiritual center of the Usora Croats -- the 
parish church of St. Anthony in Sivsa -- are coming under the 
fiercest attacks. Considerable material damage has been caused 
to residential buildings. 

</TEXT>

