<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Continue Offensive Against Teslic, Doboj </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Continue Offensive Against Teslic, Doboj </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404233694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2239 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0404233694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Banja Luka, April 4 (TANJUG)--Bosnian Moslems are 
continuing to attack on most fronts, with the brunt of the 
offensive directed against the areas of Teslic, Mt. Ozren and 
Doboj in the north, Bosnian Serb army sources said late on 
Monday. 
  The Moslems have intensified attacks on the Serb positions 
in 
northern Bosnia as part of an all-out offensive, launched with 
the object of taking the Sava River valley and cutting off a 
corridor linking the eastern and western parts of the Bosnian 
Serb republic. 
  The Bosnian Serb army command in Banja Luka reported the 
worst fighting to be in the Teslic area, where infantry attacks 
on the southern and southeastern sectors of the front were 
preceded by heavy artillery shellings. 
  Moslem forces have stepped up operations also on the 
southwestern sector of the Ozren front and on the southern 
slopes of Mt. Ozren, in an effort to break through the Serb 
defence lines, the source said. 
  Heavy artillery and infantry operations were reported also 
on 
the Doboj front, with the Moslems dropping several shells on the 
town of Doboj itself. There were no casualties, the report 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

