<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Report Muslim Troops Deserting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Report Muslim Troops Deserting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404202194 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2001 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0404202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, April 4 (TANJUG) -- Following seven days of 
fruitless efforts by Moslem forces to penetrate Serb lines with 
offensive infantry and artillery attacks from Gorazde, a United 
Nations protected area in eastern Bosnia, the troops are 
panicking and deserting, Bosnian Serb military sources have said. 
  In the area of the village of Trebesevo on Monday the local 
command of the troops loyal to Bosnian Moslem Leader Alija 
Izetbegovic ordered four Moslem troops to be shot after they 
abandoned their positions, the sources said. 
  The Moslem offensive is aimed at Cajnice, Foca and Rogatici, 
and the heaviest fighting on Monday took place in the area of 
the villages of Podkozarje and Oglecevo. 
  Moslem troops began an offensive on the Bosnian Serb 
republic 
in the second half of March, after they signed an agreement with 
Bosnian Croats on setting up a Moslem-Croat federation in 
Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7729 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu065_i_94028" </HT>


