<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Warn Croats To Stop Attacking Positions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Warn Croats To Stop Attacking Positions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504122394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1042 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Zvornik, Bratunac, 5 Apr (TANJUG) -- An all-out 
Muslim offensive against the Srpska republic in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina with the Croatian support from the left bank 
of the Sava river is continuing, but the signs that it will be 
crushed have already become obvious, a TANJUG correspondent 
learned today from the circles close to the general staff of the 
army of the Srpska republic. 
  These circles have warned that "unless the regular Army of 
the Republic of Croatia halts its attacks on all Serb defense 
lines in Posavina [region along the Sava river] today," "the 
Srpska army will retaliate," from which the Serb side has 
refrained so far. 
  This means, the circles have said, that the army of the 
Srpska republic "would begin with actions with all their forces 
and from all means at their disposal against the territory of 
the Republic of Croatia," as "attacks from long-range artillery 
and missiles systems from the left bank of the Sava river have 
been incessant over the past three days." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

