<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Than 50% Approve of Meciar's Dismissal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Than 50% Approve of Meciar's Dismissal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604084794 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 30 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0604084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "ab": "What a Survey Showed"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--According to a representative 
public-opinion survey carried out by the Focus Agency--the 
Center for Social and Marketing Analysis--33.9 percent of 
respondents definitely agree with the dismissal of Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar. Between 16 and 23 March, 1,066 
respondents were asked their view of the dismissal of Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar by the National Council of the Slovak 
Republic. Another 17.5 percent "rather agree," 16.4 percent 
"rather disagree," 24.3 percent "definitely disagree" with the 
dismissal, and 7.8 percent of respondents are unable to assess 
the situation. The Focus Agency made the results of the survey 
available to our editorial office yesterday. 

</TEXT>

