  [Text] Representatives of the Israeli Knesset and the 
Paramilitary and Security Committee of our Chamber of Deputies 
had talks in Prague today on parliamentary control of 
intelligence services. 
  According to the chairman of the Israeli committee, the 
Knesset is informed every month about the activity of the 
Israeli intelligence service Mossad. The guests were also 
interested in the change of the structure of our Army. Chairman 
of the Committee Vladimir Suman said about this, among other 
things, that the reason for the existence of the Czech Army is 
the uncertain development in the countries of the former USSR, 
organized crime, and aggressive nationalism, especially on the 
territory of the former Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

