<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Silesia Solidarity: Protests To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Silesia Solidarity: Protests To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504174194 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1700 
GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The presidium of the Silesia-Dabrowa Regional Main 
Board of Solidarity has met in Katowice. Regional Chairman 
Marek Kempski said that protest action will continue in the 
mining industry, and the way in which the government examines 
the trade unionists' demands will be of decisive significance 
for the fate of the protest action. 

</TEXT>

