BFN 

  [Excerpt] Banja Luka, 5 Apr (TANJUG) -- Muslim forces have 
resumed their offensive activities against Serb lines in the 
zone of responsibility of the First Krajina Corps of the Srpska 
republic army today, the information service of the corps said 
in Banja Luka this evening. The strongest Muslim attacks have 
been registered at the Ozren battlefield, particularly at its 
southern part in the Vozuca area. 
  Reinforced by fresh units and with artillery backing, Muslim 
forces attempted to break through the Serb lines at this part of 
the front. 
  The Teslic battlefield was not peaceful today either because 
of fierce attacks by the Muslim army on almost all parts of the 
front in which 82-mm mortars, and antiaircraft and infantry 
weapons were used. The fiercest attacks were launched northeast 
of Teslic. 
  Muslim attacks were resumed west of Doboj and 82-mm mortars 
were used. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

