<H3> <TI>   Srpska Army Continues Offensive in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Srpska Army Continues Offensive in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604085094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0736 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 6 Apr (TANJUG)-- Joint forces of the army 
of the Srpska republic this morning continued offensive actions 
from the direction of Cajnice and Foca towards Drina in an 
attempt to liberate Serb villages in the area of Podkozara, the 
command of the Srpska army in Cajnice has announced. 
  The turnabout in fighting in the Gorazde, Foca, and Cajnice 
triangle took place yesterday afternoon when the Serb fighters 
smashed the eight-day offensive of the Muslim army, which is in 
a panicked retreat towards the River Drina. 
  Without suffering any losses, the Serb fighters liberated 
the 
village of Biljin, half a km away from Vitkovici, in an 
unstoppable attack from the direction of Paljika and Trebinjaca 
yesterday evening, the command says. 
  Military police are deployed on the bridge in Vitkovici and 
are preventing the retreating Muslim soldiers from crossing to 
the left bank of the Drina River. 
  The command of the joint forces of the Srpska army says that 
the Muslim army yesterday suffered huge losses in manpower, thus 
denying reports by Muslim media about civilian casualties. 

</TEXT>

