<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Hurricane Artillery Attack' Described </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Hurricane Artillery Attack' Described </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604110194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0604110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mustafa Kurtovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] As we are sending this report, the hurricane 
artillery attack that the aggressor launched this morning on the 
defense lines on the right bank of the Drina River is being 
extended on all lines of defense of the Gorazde defenders. In 
this attack the Chetniks are using the most destructive 
howitzer, mortar, and tank projectiles. The blood-soaked ground 
of the free Gorazde territory is trembling. 
  Members of the Army of Bosnia-Herzegovina under the command 
of the East Bosnian Operations Group and the units of the 
Ministry of Internal Affairs from Gorazde are still firmly 
holding their positions, expecting new attacks by the insane 
Serbo-Montenegrin infantry. 
  At the same time the aggressor is bringing fresh forces from 
the direction of Serbia and Herzegovina. Intelligence reports 
state that the aggressor has carried out a large concentrated of 
new armored-mechanized units in (?Premlje), and that it has a 
large number of new mercenaries from the army of the 
self-proclaimed Yugoslavia. 
  Fresh forces and hardware of the Herzegovina Corps are also 
concentrating in the Foca area. All this indicates that, by 
bringing fresh Chetniks, the aggressor intends to step up the 
offensive attacks on Gorazde. 
  The announced arrival of General Michael Rose, chief 
commander of the UN forces in Bosnia-Herzegovina, in Gorazde 
should and must bring about positive results in stopping further 
suffering of these people, and in the attitude of the 
international community toward Gorazde as a protected zone. The 
truth about Gorazde's suffering in the latest Chetnik offensive 
can be and is being confirmed by UN military observers and UNHCR 
representatives in Gorazde. 
  This is Mustafa Kurtovic reporting for the Radio and 
Television of Bosnia-Herzegovina from the Press Center of the 
Gorazde District. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

