<H3> <TI>   Serbs Halt Muslim Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Halt Muslim Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504172594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1644 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cajnice, 5 Apr (TANJUG) -- The army of the Srpska 
republic today halted the eight-day offensive by Muslim forces 
toward Cajnice, Foca, and Visegrad, and undertook a 
counteroffensive, the headquarters of the Herzegovina Corps 
announced this evening. 
  The same source says Muslim soldiers are withdrawing toward 
the Drina, where strong police forces, which are not allowing 
them to cross over to the left bank of this river, are waiting 
for them on all bridges. 
  The defeat of the Muslim forces was also admitted today by 
Ferid Buljubasic, commander of the eastern Bosnia corps, and he 
sought help from the international community. 
  At 0900 this morning, the headquarters of the Serb forces 
says, two NATO aircraft violated the air space of the Srpska 
republic throughout the whole area of the upper Drina valley at 
the impermissible altitude of 600 meters. If this happens 
again, the headquarters of the Serb army says, such aircraft 
will be shot down. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

