<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Suffer Heavy Losses </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Suffer Heavy Losses </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604091694 </F>
<F P=103> AU0604091694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Network in Serbo-Croatian at 0800 GMT on 6 April carries within 
its regular 8-minute newscast several reports on the combat 
situation in the republic. 
  According to Gorazde correspondent Enes Murtovic, "the 
beginning of the ninth day of the latest and the fiercest 
offensive on Gorazde does not hold out hope that the 
Serbo-Montenegrins will easily give up their aim, which is to 
capture Gorazde. By capturing the town Slobodan Milosevic and 
Radovan Karadzic would round off the borders of the phantom 
Srpska republic, whose borders are marked with blood and [word 
indistinct] of innocent people from this region. Last night the 
aggressor fiercely attacked Borova and (?Gosun) with all 
available means from the direction of Ustipraca. Dobrijevici 
and Razalice were attacked from Mesici. After fierce fighting 
and after inflicting heavy losses on the aggressor, the 
defenders of Gorazde repelled several infantry attacks by the 
Chetniks between Ustipraca and Mesici." 
  Murtovic also reports that "this morning the Chetniks have 
continued their fierce attacks in the Gorazde area. All the 
front lines of the Gorazde defenders between Foca, Cajnice, 
Ustipraca, and Rogatica are being targeted. The Gorazde city 
center was spared destructive shells this morning, probably 
because General Michael Rose, commander of UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces], is expected to arrive here." 
  Bihac correspondent Mirza Sadikovic reports that "since last 
night, Karadzic's terrorists have continued their artillery 
attacks in the Bihac region. The target of their artillery and 
tanks deployed in Grabez are Bihac and [words indistinct] 
surrounding area. Civilians and civilian houses, as well as 
vital communications, are again being targeted." 
  The correspondent also says that "on the front lines facing 
the paramilitary formations of the so-called Kladusa autonomous 
region, small arms provocations and the shelling of the Cajnici 
area and Krivaja in the Cazin commune have continued." 
  According to a correspondent from the free territory of 
Brcko, "the Serbian aggressor has continued shelling the defense 
lines and regrouping his forces. Last night, the Chetniks 
attacked the central part of the Brcko defense lines with 60-mm 
and 82-mm mortars and portable rocket launchers." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

