<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   2,000 Bosnians Lose Refugee Status </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    2,000 Bosnians Lose Refugee Status </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504174394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a decision by the government's Office 
for Displaced Persons and Refugees, on 1 April 1994 refugees 
from Mostar lost their refugee status in the Republic of Croatia 
and will have to leave hotels and holiday facilities in the 
areas of Ploce and the Makarska riviera, the Ploce regional 
Office for Displaced Persons and Refugees has announced. 
  The majority of the 2,000 refugees from the Mostar area have 
been accommodated in hotels and other holiday facilities. 
Because of the Easter vacation, many learned about this 
decision too late to leave. Many whose homes have been destroyed 
have expressed concern about the decision because they have no 
home to return to. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

