<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Increasing Obstacles To Trade With Slovenia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Increasing Obstacles To Trade With Slovenia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504151794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1218 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ljubljana, 5 Mar (TANJUG) -- The Ministry of 
Communications of The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
[FYROM] has banned the Slovene company, Adria Airways, from 
transporting passengers and goods from the FYROM to third 
countries. 
  From today, Adria's aircraft may fly from the FYROM only on 
regular flights to Slovenia and back. Air crews are allowed to 
stay overnight in Skopje. 
  The FYROM is demanding from Slovenia the same conditions for 
its air passengers [sentence as received]. 
  In a liberally minded way, Skopje and Ljubljana have until 
recently been promising great tolerance in reciprocal business 
and other contacts, especially in trade. Over the past few 
months, however, there have been an increasing number of 
obstacles to business between the two economies with each 
wanting to make a profit off of the other. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

