<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Agreement Concluded With Hungary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic Agreement Concluded With Hungary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604114794 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1000 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Announcer] A trade agreement was concluded 
between Slovenia and Hungary. Kata Peli Nagy reports from 
Ljubljana: 
  [Peli Nagy] In six years time, Hungary and Slovenia will 
trade industrial products without customs duty and other trade 
obstacles. Although the agreement will come to force on 1 June, 
the process of dismantling customs levies will take place 
gradually. [passage omitted] 
  Through this agreement, which was signed about an hour ago 
by 
Bela Kadar, minister of international economic relations, and 
Slovenian Deputy Prime Minister Davorin Kracun in the government 
office in Ljubljana, an unhampered economic cooperation was 
established between the two countries. [passage omitted] 
  During the two years of its independence, Slovenia has 
increased its trade with Hungary by 20 percent. [passage 
omitted] The value of Slovenian exports to Hungary last year was 
$62 million and Hungary's exports to Slovenia was $139 million. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

