<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRY Army Arrests Three </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRY Army Arrests Three </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504143294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1239 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 5 Apr (TANJUG) -- Around 1115 hours 
yesterday morning Yugoslav Army border guards arrested three 
persons belonging to the UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] 
civilian police in the village of Slavujevac, three kilometers 
away from the border between the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia 
[FRY] and The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM], 
because they had crossed the border without authorization, the 
information service of the Yugoslav Army General Staff says in a 
statement issued today. 
  Two policemen and a female interpreter who illegally crossed 
the state border in a motorized vehicle were kept in the 
Slavujevac watchtower where they were questioned about their 
motives and reasons for crossing into FRY territory. Around 
1430 hours three UNPROFOR armored personnel carriers entered 300 
meters into FRY territory. Following an energetic action by 
Yugoslav Army border guards, the armored personnel carriers were 
returned to their base on FYROM territory, the statement says. 

</TEXT>

