<H3> <TI>   Committee Sets Times for Radio `Warning Strike' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Sets Times for Radio `Warning Strike' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704114194 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1000 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There is a warning strike under way in Hungarian 
Radio, called by the Independent Trade Union of Radio Employees. 
The "Chronicle" program will fulfill its public service duty and 
report on the main news briefly. The strike committee of the 
Independent Trade Union of Radio Employees called for a warning 
strike today because of economic events that have put employees 
in a disadvantegous situation. 
  The trade union does not want the warning strike to disturb 
the program order of the radio prior to the elections, so 
everything will be conducted according to the strike regulations 
in force. 
  The strike committee operating in Hungarian Radio called for 
two two-hour warning strikes: from 1100 to 1300 hours and for 
those working in the afternoon, from 1700 to 1900 hours. 
According to the communique of the strike committee, the 
objective of the warning strike is to initiate the success of 
the negotiations between the leadership of Hungarian Radio and 
organizations representing the employees and the protection of 
the radio employees' economic and social interests. 

</TEXT>

