<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Commanders, Tinca Planning `Restoration' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Commanders, Tinca Planning `Restoration' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604114294 Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA in Romanian 2 Apr 94 p 
3 </F>

<F P=103> AU0604114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Claudiu Harcioaga: "Restoration Is Being </F>
Prepared in the Army -- The Slave of the Power"] 
  [Text] A number of young army officers, the names of whom 
we will not disclose to protect them, have warned us that 
important changes will be carried out within the leadership of 
the Romanian Armed Forces. Thus, commanders of various units 
are to be replaced with "political commissaries of the Ceausescu 
era," under the pretext that during their lengthy careers and 
especially after 1989 the latter "distinguished" themselves by 
not making any mistakes. The same sources revealed that this 
genuine restoration is to take place with the consent of the new 
defense minister, Mr. Gheorghe Tinca, whom the military consider 
"the slave of the power," and that the move is part of Romania's 
"new" military orientation distinguishable over the past month, 
intended to establish a full-scale alliance with Russia. 
  Considering that Mr. Adrian Nastase [speaker of the Chamber 
of Deputies and executive chairman of the Social Democracy Party 
of Romania] is also pleading for the replacement of the army 
commanders appointed by the former defense minister [Lieutenant 
General Niculae Spiroiu], there are no more doubts left as to 
the efforts made by the state power to place the armed forces 
under its authority. 

</TEXT>

