<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Weapons Withdrawal Begins in Western Slavonia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Weapons Withdrawal Begins in Western Slavonia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604165894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1417 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Knin, 6 Apr (TANJUG) -- In western Slavonia, both 
sides [Krajina Serbs and Croats] today started to withdraw heavy 
weapons 10 or 20 km, Officer Branko Opacic from the Serb Krajina 
army's general staff told TANJUG. 
  The withdrawal -- envisaged by the Zagreb cease-fire 
agreement -- had been delayed because of a misunderstanding 
concerning the interpretation of a number of clauses of this 
agreement, but all problems were resolved on the spot by joint 
commissions. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

